reviews.text:
Stumbled in here looking for a half pint and a quick bite before dinner and found the most incredible pie I’ve ever had. Mushroom and chicken with the most buttery and flaky crust on earth. 

Quite busy on a Friday night, which is to be expected. Great service and everyone was friendly. 

I would suggest coming here for a full meal. We split this and it was the perfect amount to keep the engine running.
Great original British pub. Great burgers : try the Nicholson's beef burger... terrific!
Great food! Nice staff. I recommend the Ploughman's sharer board.
Bloody good.  Halloumi fries were the best I've ever had

Seriously fantastic food with perfect ambience and decor. The wife and I had to wait a hot minute for seats but were able to quickly grab drinks to hold us over until they were available. Food came out quickly and was spectacular. All in all a fantastic visit that will likely be repeated during our stay in London.
